{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Use British English|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Little Big Shots UK | image = Little Big Shots UK title screen.png | caption = | genre = {{plainlist| * [[Children's television series|Children]] * [[Talk show]] * [[Talent show]] }} | creator = {{plainlist| * [[Ellen DeGeneres]] * [[Steve Harvey]] }} | creative_director = Liam Lunniss | director = {{plainlist| * Liz Clare (Series 1) * Ollie Bartlett (Series 2) }} | editor = {{Plainlist| * Dominic Bell * Scott Edwards * Matt Pratt * Mike Brierly }} | writer = {{Plainlist| * Lee Stuart Evans * Alan Connor }} | based_on = {{based on|''[[Little Big Shots]]''|[[Ellen DeGeneres]] and [[Steve Harvey]]}} | presenter = [[Dawn French]] | voices = | judges = | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = English | num_seasons = 2 | num_episodes = 11 (as of 20 May 2018) | producer = {{plainlist| * Andy Rowe * Emma Taylor }} | camera = Multiple | audio_format = [[Stereo]] | runtime = 60 minutes <small>(inc. adverts)</small> | location = [[BBC Studioworks]] | company = [[Wall to Wall Media (production company)|Wall to Wall]] | distributor = [[Warner Bros. Television Productions UK]] | network = [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]] | picture_format = [[High-definition television|HDTV]] [[1080i]] | first_aired = {{Start date|2017|3|1|df=yes}} | last_aired = present | related = ''[[Little Big Shots]]'' }}
'''''Little Big Shots''''' (also known as '''''Little Big Shots with Dawn French''''') is a British [[television]] [[talent show]] that premiered on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]] on 1 March 2017. The series is hosted by [[Dawn French]] and based on the [[Little Big Shots|American show of the same name]] created by [[Ellen DeGeneres]] and [[Steve Harvey]] who is also the host of the original.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dawn French to host Little Big Shots on ITV|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/press-releases/dawn-french-host-little-big-shots-itv|accessdate=2 March 2017|work=[[itv.com]]|date=25 August 2016}}</ref> The series is produced by [[Wall to Wall Media (production company)|Wall to Wall]]. In June 2017, it was confirmed it would return for a second series, also with six episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/news/2017/06/08/36742/itv_orders_more_little_big_shots|title=ITV orders more Little Big Shots : News 2017 : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide|first=Powder Blue Internet Business|last=Solutions|website=www.chortle.co.uk}}</ref>
==Format== The show, unlike shows such as ''[[The X Factor (UK TV series)|The X Factor]]'', has no judges, winners or losers. In each episode, [[Dawn French]] talks to a 3–13 year old child about their talent, before the child performs it in front of a studio audience. Some talents shown include singing, dancing, cooking and karate.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/press-releases/little-big-shots|title=Little Big Shots|publisher=}}</ref>
