==Reception== ''Little Big Shots'' received positive reviews. Viewers said that the show "lifted the spirit" and "[was a] ray of sunshine".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.ie/style/celebrity/celebrity-news/dawn-french-hailed-for-little-big-shots-talent-show-35494392.html|title=Dawn French hailed for Little Big Shots talent show - Independent.ie|publisher=}}</ref> [[Tim Dowling]] from ''[[The Guardian]]'' said "''Little Big Shots'' appears to be the kind of cheap and cheerful fare designed to be broken into viral chunks and slapped up on YouTube afterwards: heartwarming moments from a sickly-sweet box of delights."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/mar/02/little-big-shot-dawn-french-kids-talent-show|title=Little Big Shots review: Dawn French’s cheap and cheerful talent show for children|first=Tim|last=Dowling|date=2 March 2017|website=the Guardian}}</ref>
