{{for|information about the UK-based chamber opera company|Opera a la Carte (UK)}} '''Opera a la Carte''' is a Los Angeles-based [[Gilbert and Sullivan]] professional touring [[repertory]] company. It was founded in 1970 by British Gilbert and Sullivan artist Richard Sheldon (1935–2016), who directed its productions as closely as possible to the style and practice of the original productions of the [[Savoy operas]] by the [[D'Oyly Carte Opera Company]].<ref name=SheldonObit>[http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/latimes/obituary.aspx?pid=177283021 "Obituaries: Richard Sheldon"], ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', January 14, 2016</ref> Sheldon retired from Opera a la Carte in 2014.<ref>[http://www.operaalacarte.org/about-opera-a-la-carte/richard-sheldon/ "Richard Sheldon"], Opera a la Carte, accessed January 14, 2016</ref> The company often presents ''[[H.M.S. Pinafore]]'', ''[[The Pirates of Penzance]]'' and ''[[The Mikado]]''.<ref>[http://www.operaalacarte.org/about-opera-a-la-carte/recent-performances "Recent Performances"], Opera a la Carte, accessed August 29, 2016</ref>
As of 2016, Opera a la Carte continues to tour in the United States presenting its "traditional" style Gilbert and Sullivan productions.<ref name=SheldonObit/><ref>[http://www.liedcenter.org/documents/Lied_0708_OperaALaCarte_release.pdf "Opera a la Carte Brings Best of Gilbert and Sullivan Back to Lied Center"], University of Nebraska–Lincoln, February 8, 2008; and [http://www.qcc.cuny.edu/QPAC/mikado.html Listing for the company's ''Mikado''] in New York City in April 2009, at Queensborough Performing Arts Center</ref>
